From 9d840a4829edb7b56171c64bfb5d846042451843 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jason Gross <jason@theorem.dev>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 22:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 10/10] arm: bounded inline/.S assembler sufficient to build
 musl-1.1.24

The fork's arm-asm.c is a stub whose every entry point calls
tcc_error("ARM asm not implemented."). musl's arch/arm layer needs a
real one: the crt _start, the syscall register-var dance
(`register long r7 __asm__("r7")` + `svc 0`), the v6/v7 atomics
(ldrex/strex/dmb/clz/rbit), the TLS-pointer read (mrc p15, ...), and
the bootstrap setjmp.S / longjmp.S (stmia/ldmia/bx + conditional mov).

This implements exactly that surface and errors loudly on anything
outside it (the STAGE A/B/C header comment marks the syscall, crt, and
atomics tiers). The operand/constraint machinery
(asm_compute_constraints, subst_asm_operand, the priority sort) follows
mainline tinycc's arm-asm.c structure; the register-move emission is
reimplemented to target hardware regs r0..r15 directly via o(), because
tcc-arm's load()/store() (through intr()) only model r0-r3 and r12 --
and musl pins r4-r7 as syscall register-vars, which the generic path
cannot reach.

New file arm-tok.h defines the whitelisted register / alias /
coprocessor tokens and the mnemonics (the register range is kept
contiguous for asm_parse_regvar); tcctok.h includes it under
TCC_TARGET_ARM. The "Q" memory constraint is deliberately not
implemented -- musl's two "Q" sites are patched to `"r"(ptr)` +
explicit `[%N]` (patches/musl-1.1.24-arm/atomic-no-q.patch), which the
plain-register path handles.

Scope / honesty: this is a bootstrap-grade assembler, not a general ARM
assembler; the header comment and the loud errors say so. It is
validated by a gcc-built stand-in tcc of this exact source, which
compiles + links + runs a musl hello-world and builds a reduced musl
libc.a whose binaries run under qemu-arm. The bootstrap-grade gate --
this same source MesCC-built in the milestone-3 chain, then the
from-seed boot2==boot3 fixpoint replay -- is PENDING.
